Typeof Type Operator # The typeof type operator # JavaScript already has a typeof operator you can use in an expression context:
// Prints &#34;string&#34; console.log(typeof &#34;Hello world&#34;); TypeScript adds a typeof operator you can use in a type context to refer to the type of a variable or property:
let s = &#34;hello&#34;; let n: typeof s; This isn&rsquo;t very useful for basic types, but combined with other type operators, you can use typeof to conveniently express many patterns.

